    "summary": "On January 7, 2021 at approximately 1330 hours, a Total Safety employee contracted by Fieldwood Energy LLC broke his right leg (fractured fibula and tibia) while attempting to change a combustible sensor head on a gas detector located on a generator package at SM 149 C. The employee's right foot slipped off piping while he was positioned to access the sensor, causing him to fall with his foot trapped between the generator housing and piping.",
